---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';

const article = { author: "Maine Dispensary Guide Editorial Team", publishDate: "2026-01-21", modifiedDate: "2026-03-22", section: "Compliance & Legal" };
---

<Layout 
  title="Maine Cannabis Marketing Compliance | Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="Expert guide to cannabis marketing compliance for Maine dispensary owners. Learn about advertising rules, digital marketing restrictions, and branding best practices."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1460925895917-afdab827c52f?q=80&w=2015&auto=format&fit=crop"
  article={article}
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Maine Cannabis Marketing Compliance</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Advertising rules and signage regulations for Maine dispensaries</p>
    </div>

    <section class="fact-box">
      <h2>📋 Marketing Checklist</h2>
      <table>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>Legal Basis</strong></td><td>28-B M.R.S. §701, OCP Rule Chapter 6</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Minimum Age</strong></td><td>All marketing must target 21+</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Required Warning</strong></td><td>"For use only by adults 21+" on all ads</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Billboard Ban</strong></td><td>Prohibited on I-95 and federal highways</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>School Buffer</strong></td><td>No advertising within 500 ft of schools</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Social Media</strong></td><td>Age-gating REQUIRED on all platforms</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Why Compliance Matters</h2>
      <p>Marketing violations can result in license suspension, fines, and mandated corrective action. But here's the opportunity: operators who master compliant marketing build trust with regulators AND customers. Compliance becomes a competitive advantage.</p>
    </section>

    <Callout title="Creativity Within Boundaries" type="passion">
      Maine's marketing rules exist to protect minors while allowing adult access. Master these rules, and you'll build a brand that regulators trust and customers respect.
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>The Dos and Don'ts</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>✅ DO</th><th>❌ DON'T</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Include "21+" warning on EVERY ad</td><td>Use cartoon characters or kid appeal imagery</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Age-gate all digital marketing</td><td>Advertise on Billboard (I-95 prohibited)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Target 25+ demographics on Meta/Google</td><td>Claim cannabis cures diseases</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Use educational content marketing</td><td>Use testimonials or endorsements</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Build local SEO presence</td><td>Advertise within 500 ft of schools</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Legal Framework: 28-B M.R.S. §701</h2>
      <p>Under <strong>Maine Statute 28-B §701</strong> and <strong>OCP Rule Chapter 6</strong>:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>All advertising must include health warning</li>
        <li>No targeting minors (anyone under 21)</li>
        <li>No false or misleading claims</li>
        <li>No mass-market advertising that reaches minors</li>
        <li>Must comply with federal advertising restrictions</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Platform-Specific Rules</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Platform</th><th>Rule</th><th>Pro-Hack</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>Google Ads</strong></td><td>Cannabis-friendly policy, 21+ targeting</td><td>Target "cannabis near me" terms</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Meta (FB/IG)</strong></td><td>Age-restricted, no paid cannabis ads</td><td>Build organic following, use hashtags</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Billboard</strong></td><td>Banned on federal highways</td><td>Check local Portland/Bangor rules</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Print</strong></td><td>Must be in 21+ publications</td><td>Local alt-weeklies work well</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Radio</strong></td><td>Restricted hours (10pm-4am)</td><td>Consider podcast sponsorships</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Pro-Hack: The "Educational First" Strategy</h2>
      <p><strong>The compliant content marketing play:</strong> Instead of selling products, create educational content about cannabis. Blog posts about "how to choose the right strain" or "understanding THC vs CBD" build trust without triggering compliance issues.</p>
      <p><strong>Why it works:</strong> Educational content is explicitly protected under OCP rules. It attracts customers organically and demonstrates your commitment to responsible use.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Signage Rules: Local Adds Complexity</h2>
      <p>Maine allows signage, but LOCAL rules vary significantly:</p>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>City</th><th>Signage Rule</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Portland</td><td>Strict limitations, council approval often required</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Bangor</td><td>Standard commercial rules apply</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Lewiston</td><td>Requires special permit</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Augusta</td><td>Moderate restrictions</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p><strong>Pro-Hack:</strong> Always check with local code enforcement BEFORE ordering signage.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>✅ Required:</strong> "21+" warning on EVERY advertisement</li>
        <li><strong>⚠️ Banned:</strong> Billboards on I-95, cartoon characters, medical claims</li>
        <li><strong>📱 Digital:</strong> Age-gating mandatory on all social media</li>
        <li><strong>📍 Local:</strong> Check city signage rules—they vary significantly</li>
        <li><strong>💡 Strategy:</strong> Educational content = compliant + effective</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Resources</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/adult-use/rules" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OCP Rules Chapter 6</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-license/">License Guide</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/maine-cannabis-real-estate/">Real Estate Guide</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Verify current requirements with OCP.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
